  "title": "In C — Terry Riley (1964)",
  "description": "13-voice generative performance of Terry Riley's *In C*. A conductor agent observes the ensemble and decides when each voice moves between the 53 cells, with a deterministic fallback script keeping the piece listenable when no LLM backend is available. A constant C5 8th-note pulse anchors the ensemble. Mixed across a 20-channel mixer through a shared reverb.",
